This paper deals with information theory and communication systems, which are typically categorized under cs.IT. The paper also discusses the concept of confidentiality, which falls under the category of cs.CR (cryptography and security). The use of multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) technology is a key aspect of the paper, which is often studied in the context of wireless communication systems and falls under the category of cs.MM (mobile and wireless computing). The paper also explores the capacity region of the channel, which is a fundamental concept in information theory and falls under the category of cs.SI (information theory). Finally, the paper deals with the transmission of messages between users, which is a topic that falls under the category of cs.NI (networking and internet architecture).
